SM   hmmsearch --cpu 8 -Z 90746521 -E 1000 HMM pfamseq
TP   Domain
CC   This entry represents a C-terminal domain (approximately 35-48
CC   residues, positions 499-547) found in the methyltransferase (M)
CC   subunit of type I restriction-modification systems. This domain
CC   follows the N6-adenine DNA methyltransferase domain (Pfam:PF02384).
CC   Type I restriction-modification systems provide bacteria with
CC   protection against foreign DNA through sequence-specific DNA
CC   methylation and restriction. The family is found in Pseudomonadota
CC   (Alphaproteobacteria, Betaproteobacteria, Gammaproteobacteria) and
CC   Bacteroidota.
